  "local_port": 44672,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What test cases management tool do you recommend to integrate with Github or Zenhub?",
  "response": "When it comes to test case management tools that integrate well with GitHub or ZenHub, there are several excellent options to consider. The best choice depends on your team's specific needs, such as ease of integration, features, pricing, and scalability. Here\u2019s a list of popular tools that integrate well with GitHub and ZenHub:\n\n---\n\n### **1. TestRail**\n- **Integration with GitHub**: TestRail offers direct integration with GitHub to link test cases to issues, pull requests, and branches.\n- **Features**: Comprehensive test case management, reporting, and traceability features.\n- **Best for**: Teams looking for a robust, enterprise-grade test management solution.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Zephyr Scale**\n- **Integration with GitHub**: Zephyr Scale integrates seamlessly with GitHub via Jira (which connects to ZenHub). It allows linking test cases to issues and pull requests.\n- **Features**: Agile-focused test management, scalable for large teams, and supports advanced reporting.\n- **Best for**: Teams already using Jira and looking for a scalable test management solution.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Qase**\n- **Integration with GitHub**: Qase offers native GitHub integration, enabling test case updates based on GitHub issues and pull requests.\n- **Features**: Modern UI, test execution tracking, and robust reporting.\n- **Best for**: Teams looking for a user-friendly, cloud-based test management tool.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Xray**\n- **Integration with GitHub**: Xray integrates with GitHub via Jira (which connects to ZenHub). It links test cases to issues and pull requests.\n- **Features**: Supports both manual and automated testing, traceability, and advanced reporting.\n- **Best for**: Teams already using Jira and looking for extensive test management capabilities.\n\n---\n\n### **5. PractiTest**\n- **Integration with GitHub**: PractiTest integrates with GitHub through APIs, enabling linking test cases to issues and pull requests.\n- **Features**: Customizable dashboards, traceability, and integrations with other tools.\n- **Best for**: Teams looking for a flexible, customizable test management platform.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Katalon TestOps**\n- **Integration with GitHub**: Katalon TestOps integrates with GitHub to manage test cases and link them to issues and pull requests.\n- **Features**: Test automation orchestration, reporting, and analytics.\n- **Best for**: Teams focused on test automation and CI/CD pipelines.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Testmo**\n- **Integration with GitHub**: Testmo offers GitHub integration, enabling test case updates based on issues and pull requests.\n- **Features**: Modern UI, test execution tracking, and reporting.\n- **Best for**: Teams looking for a lightweight, modern test management solution.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Allure TestOps**\n- **Integration with GitHub**: Allure TestOps integrates with GitHub to manage test cases and link them to issues and pull requests.\n- **Features**: Advanced reporting, test automation support, and traceability.\n- **Best for**: Teams focused on test automation and CI/CD pipelines.\n\n---\n\n### **How to Choose the Right Tool**\n1. **Integration**: Ensure the tool integrates seamlessly with GitHub and ZenHub.\n2. **Features**: Look for features like test case management, reporting, traceability, and automation support.\n3. **Pricing**: Compare pricing plans to find one that fits your budget.\n4. **Scalability**: Consider the tool\u2019s ability to grow with your team.\n5. **User Experience**: Choose a tool with a user-friendly interface and good support.\n\n---\n\nIf you\u2019re already using ZenHub, tools that integrate with Jira (like Zephyr Scale or Xray) may be a good fit since ZenHub is built on top of Jira. Otherwise, tools like TestRail, Qase, or Testmo offer direct GitHub integration and may be more straightforward to set up.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
